OL,3,C'I feel like a second class citizen' -
OL,4,Cguide dog user speaks out after taxi
OL,5,Csnub
OL,7,F"Guide dogs are highly trained
OL,8,Fanimals, they're not just simply pets.
OL,9,FFor a person living with sight loss
OL,10,Fthey're a vital mobility aid that
OL,11,Fprovides a sense of freedom and
OL,12,Findependence for them to feel they can
OL,13,Fget around safely."
OL,15,FCallum Sullivan, a driver for Vale
OL,16,FTaxis, believes better awareness
OL,17,Ftraining is needed: "It's only in the
OL,18,Fhandbook that you get given after
OL,19,Fyou've passed. You don't get sat down
OL,20,Fand told you have to take guide dogs.
